            <h5 class="column-head feature" data-uuid="0033429c7cf644739cadabcad485da9a"><span>The Energy Crisis</span><span>&#160;</span></h5>
            <p class="intro-feature" data-uuid="0e617e5638144c2482a307ae8d20811e"><span>Rising oil prices in the early 1970s had a major&#160;</span><span>impact on the U.S. economy. Because oil was more expensive, the&#160;</span><span>cost of everything made from oil&#160;</span><span>—</span><span>gasoline, heating oil, electricity,</span><span>and other key products</span><span>—</span><span>also shot up. These</span><span>&#160;</span><span>higher prices led to&#160;</span><span>rising inflation.</span><br />
            </p>
