        <p data-uuid="e3cc913e0a134f1f86db8897405c7cf7">Most OPEC countries were Arab countries that
            had been opposed to the creation of the Jewish state of Israel. On October 6,
            1973, the Jewish holy day of Yom Kippur, Egypt and Syria attacked Israel. The
            attack started what would become known as the Yom Kippur War. The United States
            sent military supplies to help Israel.</p>
        <p data-uuid="d9f413536981460897a2eff32739aff6">
            Arab members of OPEC responded angrily to support for Israel. They
            declared an embargo, or ban, on oil sales to the United States. The oil embargo
            and soaring oil prices caused an energy crisis. This worsened an already weak
            U.S. economy.<br />
        </p>
